{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["66-REV-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"REV"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Revelation \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Revelation to Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Revelation \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Rev \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["The Revelation to Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"REV 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 1:1"},"This is the Revelation of Al Masih Isa, which Allah gave him to show to his servants the things which must happen soon,\nwhich he sent and made known by his angel",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, messenger (here and wherever angel is\nmentioned)"]}],"caller":"+"}," to his servant, Yuhanna, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 1:2"},"who testified to Allah’s word and of the testimony of Al Masih Isa, about everything that he saw.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 1:3"},"Blessed is he who reads and those who hear the words of the prophecy, and keep the things that are written in it, for the\ntime is at hand. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 1:4"},"Yuhanna, to the seven assemblies that are in Asia: Grace to you and peace from Allah, who is and who was and who is to\ncome; and from the seven Spirits who are before his throne; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 1:5"},"and from Al Masih Isa, the faithful witness, the firstborn of the dead, and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To him\nwho loves us, and washed us from our sins by his blood— \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 1:6"},"and he made us to be a Kingdom, priests",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus\n19:6; Isaiah 61:6 "]}],"caller":"+"}," to his Allah and Father—to him be the glory and the dominion forever and ever. Amen.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 1:7"},"Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “ἰδοὺ”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as\nan interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," he is coming with the clouds, and every eye will see him, including those who pierced him. All the tribes\nof the earth will mourn over him. Even so, Amen. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 1:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am the Alpha and the Omega,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “the Beginning and the\nEnd”"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["”"]}," says the Lord Allah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR omits “Allah”"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“who is and who was and who is to come, the Almighty.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 1:9"},"I Yuhanna, your brother and partner with you in the oppression, Kingdom, and perseverance in Masih Isa, was on the isle\nthat is called Patmos because of Allah’s Word and the testimony of Al Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 1:10"},"I was in the Spirit on the Lord’s day, and I heard behind me a loud voice, like a trumpet\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 1:11"},"saying, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the\nLast.”"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What you see, write in a book and send to the seven\nassemblies:"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “which are in Asia”"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["to Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamum, Thyatira, Sardis, Philadelphia, and to\nLaodicea.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 1:12"},"I turned to see the voice that spoke with me. Having turned, I saw seven golden lamp stands.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 1:13"},"And amongst the lamp stands was one like a son of man,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Daniel 7:13 "]}],"caller":"+"}," clothed with a robe reaching down to his feet, and with a golden sash around his chest.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 1:14"},"His head and his hair were white as white wool, like snow. His eyes were like a flame of fire.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 1:15"},"His feet were like burnished brass, as if it had been refined in a furnace. His voice was like the voice of many waters.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 1:16"},"He had seven stars in his right hand. Out of his mouth proceeded a sharp two-edged sword. His face was like the sun\nshining at its brightest. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 1:17"},"When I saw him, I fell at his feet like a dead man. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He laid his right hand on me, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t be afraid. I am the first and the last,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 1:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and the Living one. I was dead, and behold, I am alive forever and ever. Amen. I have the keys of Death and of\nHades."]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Hell"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 1:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Write therefore the things which you have seen, and the things which are, and the things which will happen\nhereafter. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 1:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The mystery of the seven stars which you saw in my right hand, and the seven golden lamp stands is this: The seven\nstars are the angels"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, messengers (here and wherever angels are\nmentioned)"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["of the seven assemblies. The seven lamp stands are seven\nassemblies."]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"REV 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 2:1"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To the angel of the assembly in Ephesus write:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He who holds the seven stars in his right hand, he who walks amongst the seven golden lamp stands says these\nthings:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 2:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I know your works, and your toil and perseverance, and that you can’t tolerate evil men, and have tested those who\ncall themselves apostles, and they are not, and found them false.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 2:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You have perseverance and have endured for my name’s sake, and have\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “have laboured and”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["not grown weary.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 2:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I have this against you, that you left your first love.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 2:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Remember therefore from where you have fallen, and repent and do the first works; or else I am coming to you swiftly,\nand will move your lamp stand out of its place, unless you repent.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 2:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But this you have, that you hate the works of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 2:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the assemblies. To him who overcomes I will give to eat from\nthe tree of life, which is in the Paradise of my Allah."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 2:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To the angel of the assembly in Smyrna write:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The first and the last, who was dead, and has come to life says these\nthings:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 2:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I know your works, oppression, and your poverty (but you are rich), and the blasphemy of those who say they are\nJews, and they are not, but are a synagogue of Iblis. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 2:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t be afraid of the things which you are about to suffer. Behold, the Iblis is about to throw some of you into\nprison, that you may be tested; and you will have oppression for ten days. Be faithful to death, and I will give you the crown\nof life. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 2:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the assemblies. He who overcomes won’t be harmed by the\nsecond death."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 2:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To the angel of the assembly in Pergamum write:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He who has the sharp two-edged sword says these things:"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 2:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I know your works and where you dwell, where Iblis’s throne is. You hold firmly to my name, and didn’t deny my\nfaith in the days of Antipas my witness, my faithful one, who was killed amongst you, where Iblis dwells.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 2:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I have a few things against you, because you have there some who hold the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak\nto throw a stumbling block before the children of Israel, to eat things sacrificed to idols, and to commit sexual immorality.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 2:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["So you also have some who hold to the teaching of the Nicolaitans\nlikewise."]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “which I hate” instead of\n“likewise”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 2:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Repent therefore, or else I am coming to you quickly, and I will make war against them with the sword of my mouth.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 2:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the assemblies. To him who overcomes, to him I will give of\nthe hidden manna, "]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Manna is supernatural food, named after the Hebrew for “What is it?”. See\nExodus 11:7-9."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and I will give him a white stone, and on the stone a new name written, which no one knows but he who\nreceives it."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 2:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To the angel of the assembly in Thyatira write:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The Son of Allah, who has his eyes like a flame of fire, and his feet are like burnished brass, says these\nthings:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 2:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I know your works, your love, faith, service, patient endurance, and that your last works are more than the first.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 2:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I have this against you, that you tolerate your"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR, NU read “that” instead of “your”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["woman, Jezebel, who calls herself a prophetess. She teaches and\nseduces my servants to commit sexual immorality, and to eat things sacrificed to idols.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 2:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I gave her time to repent, but she refuses to repent of her sexual immorality.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"REV 2:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, I will throw her into a bed, and those who commit adultery with her into great oppression, unless they\nrepent of her works. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"REV 2:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I will kill her children with Death, and all the assemblies will know that I am he who searches the minds and\nhearts. I will give to each one of you according to your deeds. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"REV 2:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But to you I say, to the rest who are in Thyatira, as many as don’t have this teaching, who don’t know what some\ncall ‘the deep things of Iblis,’ to you I say, I am not putting any other burden on you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"REV 2:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Nevertheless, hold that which you have firmly until I come.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"REV 2:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who overcomes, and he who keeps my works to the end, to him I will give authority over the nations.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"REV 2:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He will rule them with a rod of iron, shattering them like clay\npots;"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 2:9"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["as I also have received of my Father:\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"REV 2:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and I will give him the morning star. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"REV 2:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the\nassemblies."]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"REV 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 3:1"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“And to the angel of the assembly in Sardis write:"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He who has the seven Spirits of Allah, and the seven stars says these\nthings:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I know your works, that you have a reputation of being alive, but you are dead.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 3:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Wake up, and keep the things that remain, which you were about to throw away, for I have found no works of yours\nperfected before my Allah. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 3:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Remember therefore how you have received and heard. Keep it and repent. If therefore you won’t watch, I will come as\na thief, and you won’t know what hour I will come upon you. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 3:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Nevertheless you have a few names in Sardis that didn’t defile their garments. They will walk with me in white, for\nthey are worthy. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 3:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who overcomes will be arrayed in white garments, and I will in no way blot his name out of the book of life, and I\nwill confess his name before my Father, and before his angels. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 3:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the\nassemblies."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 3:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To the angel of the assembly in Philadelphia write:"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He who is holy, he who is true, he who has the key of Dawood, he who opens and no one can shut, and who shuts and no\none opens, says these things: "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 3:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I know your works (behold, I have set before you an open door, which no one can shut), that you have a little power,\nand kept my word, and didn’t deny my name. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 3:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, I give some of the synagogue of Iblis, of those who say they are Jews, and they are not, but lie. Behold, I\nwill make them to come and worship before your feet, and to know that I have loved you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 3:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Because you kept my command to endure, I also will keep you from the hour of testing which is to come on the whole\nworld, to test those who dwell on the earth. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 3:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am coming quickly! Hold firmly that which you have, so that no one takes your crown.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 3:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who overcomes, I will make him a pillar in the temple of my Allah, and he will go out from there no more. I will\nwrite on him the name of my Allah and the name of the city of my Allah, the new Jerusalem, which comes down out of heaven from\nmy Allah, and my own new name. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 3:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the\nassemblies."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 3:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To the angel of the assembly in Laodicea write:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The Amen, the Faithful and True Witness, the Beginning"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Source, or Head"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["of Allah’s creation, says these\nthings:"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 3:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I know your works, that you are neither cold nor hot. I wish you were cold or hot.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 3:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["So, because you are lukewarm, and neither hot nor cold, I will vomit you out of my mouth.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 3:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Because you say, ‘I am rich, and have gotten riches, and have need of nothing;’ and don’t know that you are the\nwretched one, miserable, poor, blind, and naked; "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 3:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I counsel you to buy from me gold refined by fire, that you may become rich; and white garments, that you may clothe\nyourself, and that the shame of your nakedness may not be revealed; and eye salve to anoint your eyes, that you may see.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 3:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["As many as I love, I reprove and chasten. Be zealous therefore, and repent.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 3:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, I stand at the door and knock. If anyone hears my voice and opens the door, then I will come in to him, and\nwill dine with him, and he with me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 3:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who overcomes, I will give to him to sit down with me on my throne, as I also overcame, and sat down with my\nFather on his throne. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"REV 3:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the\nassemblies.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"REV 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 4:1"},"After these things I looked and saw a door opened in heaven, and the first voice that I heard, like a trumpet speaking\nwith me, was one saying, “Come up here, and I will show you the things which must happen after this.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 4:2"},"Immediately I was in the Spirit. Behold, there was a throne set in heaven, and one sitting on the throne\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 4:3"},"that looked like a jasper stone and a sardius. There was a rainbow around the throne, like an emerald to look at.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 4:4"},"Around the throne were twenty-four thrones. On the thrones were twenty-four elders sitting, dressed in white garments,\nwith crowns of gold on their heads. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 4:5"},"Out of the throne proceed lightnings, sounds, and thunders. There were seven lamps of fire burning before his throne,\nwhich are the seven Spirits of Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 4:6"},"Before the throne was something like a sea of glass, similar to crystal. In the middle of the throne, and around the\nthrone were four living creatures full of eyes before and behind.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 4:7"},"The first creature was like a lion, and the second creature like a calf, and the third creature had a face like a man, and\nthe fourth was like a flying eagle. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 4:8"},"The four living creatures, each one of them having six wings, are full of eyes around and within. They have no rest day\nand night, saying, “Holy, holy, holy",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hodges/Farstad MT reads “holy” 9 times instead of\n3."]}],"caller":"+"}," is the Lord Allah, the Almighty, who was and who is and who is to come!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 4:9"},"When the living creatures give glory, honour, and thanks to him who sits on the throne, to him who lives forever and ever,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 4:10"},"the twenty-four elders fall down before him who sits on the throne, and worship him who lives forever and ever, and throw\ntheir crowns before the throne, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 4:11"},"“Worthy are you, our Lord and Allah, the Holy One,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:11\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR omits “and Allah, the Holy One,”"]}],"caller":"+"}," to receive the glory, the honour, and the power, for you created all things, and\nbecause of your desire they existed, and were created!” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"REV 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 5:1"},"I saw, in the right hand of him who sat on the throne, a book written inside and outside, sealed shut with seven seals.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 5:2"},"I saw a mighty angel proclaiming with a loud voice, “Who is worthy to open the book, and to break its seals?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 5:3"},"No one in heaven above, or on the earth, or under the earth, was able to open the book or to look in it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 5:4"},"Then I wept much, because no one was found worthy to open the book or to look in it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 5:5"},"One of the elders said to me, “Don’t weep. Behold, the Lion who is of the tribe of Judah, the Root of Dawood, has\novercome: he who opens the book and its seven seals.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 5:6"},"I saw in the middle of the throne and of the four living creatures, and in the middle of the elders, a Lamb standing, as\nthough it had been slain, having seven horns and seven eyes, which are the seven Spirits of Allah, sent out into all the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 5:7"},"Then he came, and he took it out of the right hand of him who sat on the throne.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 5:8"},"Now when he had taken the book, the four living creatures and the twenty-four elders fell down before the Lamb, each one\nhaving a harp, and golden bowls full of incense, which are the prayers of the saints.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 5:9"},"They sang a new song, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You are worthy to take the book \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to open its seals: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for you were killed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and bought us for Allah with your blood \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["out of every tribe, language, people, and nation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 5:10"},"and made us kings and priests to our Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and we will reign on the earth.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 5:11"},"I saw, and I heard something like a voice of many angels around the throne, the living creatures, and the elders. The\nnumber of them was ten thousands of ten thousands, and thousands of thousands;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 5:12"},"saying with a loud voice, “Worthy is the Lamb who has been killed to receive the power, wealth, wisdom, strength, honour,\nglory, and blessing!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 5:13"},"I heard every created thing which is in heaven, on the earth, under the earth, on the sea, and everything in them,\nsaying, “To him who sits on the throne, and to the Lamb be the blessing, the honour, the glory, and the dominion, forever and\never! Amen!”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR omits “Amen!”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 5:14"},"The four living creatures said, “Amen!” Then the",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:14\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “twenty-four”"]}],"caller":"+"}," elders fell down and worshipped.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “the one living forever and ever”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"REV 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 6:1"},"I saw that the Lamb opened one of the seven seals, and I heard one of the four living creatures saying, as with a voice of\nthunder, “Come and see!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 6:2"},"And behold, a white horse, and he who sat on it had a bow. A crown was given to him, and he came out conquering, and to\nconquer. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 6:3"},"When he opened the second seal, I heard the second living creature saying, “Come!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 6:4"},"Another came out: a red horse. To him who sat on it was given power to take peace from the earth, and that they should\nkill one another. There was given to him a great sword. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 6:5"},"When he opened the third seal, I heard the third living creature saying, “Come and see!” And behold, a black horse, and he\nwho sat on it had a balance in his hand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 6:6"},"I heard a voice in the middle of the four living creatures saying, “A choenix\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A choenix is a dry volume measure that is a little more than a litre (a little more than a\nquart)."]}],"caller":"+"}," of wheat for a denarius, and three choenix of barley for a denarius! Don’t damage the oil and the wine!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 6:7"},"When he opened the fourth seal, I heard the fourth living creature saying, “Come and see!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 6:8"},"And behold, a pale horse, and the name of he who sat on it was Death. Hades\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Hell"]}],"caller":"+"}," followed with him. Authority over one fourth of the earth, to kill with the sword, with famine,\nwith death, and by the wild animals of the earth was given to him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 6:9"},"When he opened the fifth seal, I saw underneath the altar the souls of those who had been killed for the Word of Allah,\nand for the testimony of the Lamb which they had. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 6:10"},"They cried with a loud voice, saying, “How long, Master, the holy and true, until you judge and avenge our blood on those\nwho dwell on the earth?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 6:11"},"A long white robe was given to each of them. They were told that they should rest yet for a while, until their fellow\nservants and their brothers, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “brothers” here and where context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated “brothers and sisters” or “siblings.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," who would also be killed even as they were, should complete their course.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 6:12"},"I saw when he opened the sixth seal, and there was a great earthquake. The sun became black as sackcloth made of hair,\nand the whole moon became as blood. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 6:13"},"The stars of the sky fell to the earth, like a fig tree dropping its unripe figs when it is shaken by a great wind.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 6:14"},"The sky was removed like a scroll when it is rolled up. Every mountain and island were moved out of their places.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 6:15"},"The kings of the earth, the princes, the commanding officers, the rich, the strong, and every slave and free person, hid\nthemselves in the caves and in the rocks of the mountains. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 6:16"},"They told the mountains and the rocks, “Fall on us, and hide us from the face of him who sits on the throne, and from the\nwrath of the Lamb, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 6:17"},"for the great day of his wrath has come; and who is able to stand?”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"REV 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 7:1"},"After this, I saw four angels standing at the four corners of the earth, holding the four winds of the earth, so that no\nwind would blow on the earth, or on the sea, or on any tree. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 7:2"},"I saw another angel ascend from the sunrise, having the seal of the living Allah. He cried with a loud voice to the four\nangels to whom it was given to harm the earth and the sea, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 7:3"},"saying, “Don’t harm the earth, neither the sea, nor the trees, until we have sealed the bondservants of our Allah on their\nforeheads!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 7:4"},"I heard the number of those who were sealed, one hundred and forty-four thousand, sealed out of every tribe of the\nchildren of Israel: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 7:5"},"of the tribe of Judah twelve thousand were sealed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Reuben twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Gad twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 7:6"},"of the tribe of Asher twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Naphtali twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Manasseh twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 7:7"},"of the tribe of Simeon twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Levi twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Issachar twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 7:8"},"of the tribe of Zebulun twelve thousand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Yusuf twelve thousand, and \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of the tribe of Benjamin twelve thousand were sealed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 7:9"},"After these things I looked, and behold, a great multitude, which no man could count, out of every nation and of all\ntribes, peoples, and languages, standing before the throne and before the Lamb, dressed in white robes, with palm branches in\ntheir hands. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 7:10"},"They cried with a loud voice, saying, “Salvation be to our Allah, who sits on the throne, and to the Lamb!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 7:11"},"All the angels were standing around the throne, the elders, and the four living creatures; and they fell on their faces\nbefore his throne, and worshipped Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 7:12"},"saying, “Amen! Blessing, glory, wisdom, thanksgiving, honour, power, and might, be to our Allah forever and ever! Amen.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 7:13"},"One of the elders answered, saying to me, “These who are arrayed in the white robes, who are they, and where did they\ncome from?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 7:14"},"I told him, “My lord, you know.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to me, “These are those who came out of the great suffering.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, oppression"]}],"caller":"+"},"They washed their robes, and made them white in the Lamb’s blood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 7:15"},"Therefore they are before the throne of Allah, they serve him day and night in his temple. He who sits on the throne will\nspread his tabernacle over them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 7:16"},"They will never be hungry or thirsty any more. The sun won’t beat on them, nor any heat;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 7:17"},"for the Lamb who is in the middle of the throne shepherds them and leads them to springs of life-giving waters. And Allah\nwill wipe away every tear from their eyes.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"REV 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 8:1"},"When he opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven for about half an hour.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 8:2"},"I saw the seven angels who stand before Allah, and seven trumpets were given to them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 8:3"},"Another angel came and stood over the altar, having a golden censer. Much incense was given to him, that he should add it\nto the prayers of all the saints on the golden altar which was before the throne.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 8:4"},"The smoke of the incense, with the prayers of the saints, went up before Allah out of the angel’s hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 8:5"},"The angel took the censer, and he filled it with the fire of the altar, then threw it on the earth. Thunders, sounds,\nlightnings, and an earthquake followed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 8:6"},"The seven angels who had the seven trumpets prepared themselves to sound.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 8:7"},"The first sounded, and there followed hail and fire, mixed with blood, and they were thrown to the earth. One third of the\nearth was burnt up, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR omits “One third of the earth was burnt\nup”"]}],"caller":"+"}," and one third of the trees were burnt up, and all green grass was burnt up.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 8:8"},"The second angel sounded, and something like a great burning mountain was thrown into the sea. One third of the sea became\nblood, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 8:9"},"and one third of the living creatures which were in the sea died. One third of the ships were destroyed.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 8:10"},"The third angel sounded, and a great star fell from the sky, burning like a torch, and it fell on one third of the\nrivers, and on the springs of the waters. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 8:11"},"The name of the star is called “Wormwood.” One third of the waters became wormwood. Many people died from the waters,\nbecause they were made bitter. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 8:12"},"The fourth angel sounded, and one third of the sun was struck, and one third of the moon, and one third of the stars; so\nthat one third of them would be darkened, and the day wouldn’t shine for one third of it, and the night in the same way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 8:13"},"I saw, and I heard an eagle,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “angel” instead of “eagle”\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," flying in mid heaven, saying with a loud voice, “Woe! Woe! Woe for those who dwell on the earth, because of the other\nvoices of the trumpets of the three angels, who are yet to sound!”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"REV 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 9:1"},"The fifth angel sounded, and I saw a star from the sky which had fallen to the earth. The key to the pit of the abyss was\ngiven to him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 9:2"},"He opened the pit of the abyss, and smoke went up out of the pit, like the smoke from\na",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “great”"]}],"caller":"+"}," burning furnace. The sun and the air were darkened because of the smoke from the pit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 9:3"},"Then out of the smoke came locusts on the earth, and power was given to them, as the scorpions of the earth have power.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 9:4"},"They were told that they should not hurt the grass of the earth, neither any green thing, neither any tree, but only those\npeople who don’t have Allah’s seal on their foreheads. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 9:5"},"They were given power, not to kill them, but to torment them for five months. Their torment was like the torment of a\nscorpion when it strikes a person. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 9:6"},"In those days people will seek death, and will in no way find it. They will desire to die, and death will flee from them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 9:7"},"The shapes of the locusts were like horses prepared for war. On their heads were something like golden crowns, and their\nfaces were like people’s faces. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 9:8"},"They had hair like women’s hair, and their teeth were like those of lions.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 9:9"},"They had breastplates, like breastplates of iron. The sound of their wings was like the sound of chariots, or of many\nhorses rushing to war. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 9:10"},"They have tails like those of scorpions, and stings. In their tails they have power to harm men for five months.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 9:11"},"They have over them as king the angel of the abyss. His name in Hebrew is\n“Abaddon”,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Abaddon” is a Hebrew word that means “ruin”, “destruction”, or “the place of\ndestruction”"]}],"caller":"+"}," but in Greek, he has the name “Apollyon”. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:11\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Apollyon” means “Destroyer”."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 9:12"},"The first woe is past. Behold, there are still two woes coming after this.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 9:13"},"The sixth angel sounded. I heard a voice from the horns of the golden altar which is before Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 9:14"},"saying to the sixth angel who had the trumpet, “Free the four angels who are bound at the great river Euphrates!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 9:15"},"The four angels were freed who had been prepared for that hour and day and month and year, so that they might kill one\nthird of mankind. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 9:16"},"The number of the armies of the horsemen was two hundred million.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, “ten thousands of ten thousands”"]}],"caller":"+"}," I heard the number of them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 9:17"},"Thus I saw the horses in the vision, and those who sat on them, having breastplates of fiery red, hyacinth blue, and\nsulphur yellow; and the horses’ heads resembled lions’ heads. Out of their mouths proceed fire, smoke, and sulphur.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 9:18"},"By these three plagues were one third of mankind killed: by the fire, the smoke, and the sulphur, which proceeded out of\ntheir mouths. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 9:19"},"For the power of the horses is in their mouths and in their tails. For their tails are like serpents, and have heads, and\nwith them they harm. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 9:20"},"The rest of mankind, who were not killed with these plagues, didn’t repent of the works of their hands, that they\nwouldn’t worship demons, and the idols of gold, and of silver, and of brass, and of stone, and of wood; which can’t see, hear,\nor walk. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 9:21"},"They didn’t repent of their murders, their sorceries,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “sorceries” (pharmakeia) also implies the use of potions, poisons, and\ndrugs"]}],"caller":"+"}," their sexual immorality, or their thefts. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"REV 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 10:1"},"I saw a mighty angel coming down out of the sky, clothed with a cloud. A rainbow was on his head. His face was like the\nsun, and his feet like pillars of fire. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 10:2"},"He had in his hand a little open book. He set his right foot on the sea, and his left on the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 10:3"},"He cried with a loud voice, as a lion roars. When he cried, the seven thunders uttered their voices.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 10:4"},"When the seven thunders sounded, I was about to write; but I heard a voice from the sky saying, “Seal up the things which\nthe seven thunders said, and don’t write them.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 10:5"},"The angel whom I saw standing on the sea and on the land lifted up his right hand to the sky,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 10:6"},"and swore by him who lives forever and ever, who created heaven and the things that are in it, the earth and the things\nthat are in it, and the sea and the things that are in it, that there will no longer be delay,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 10:7"},"but in the days of the voice of the seventh angel, when he is about to sound, then the mystery of Allah is finished, as he\ndeclared to his servants, the prophets. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 10:8"},"The voice which I heard from heaven, again speaking with me, said, “Go, take the book which is open in the hand of the\nangel who stands on the sea and on the land.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 10:9"},"I went to the angel, telling him to give me the little book.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to me, “Take it, and eat it. It will make your stomach bitter, but in your mouth it will be as sweet as honey.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 10:10"},"I took the little book out of the angel’s hand, and ate it. It was as sweet as honey in my mouth. When I had eaten it, my\nstomach was made bitter. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 10:11"},"They",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “He” instead of “They”"]}],"caller":"+"}," told me, “You must prophesy again over many peoples, nations,\nlanguages, and kings.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"REV 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 11:1"},"A reed like a rod was given to me. Someone said, “Rise, and measure Allah’s temple, and the altar, and those who worship\nin it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 11:2"},"Leave out the court which is outside of the temple, and don’t measure it, for it has been given to the nations. They will\ntread the holy city under foot for forty-two months. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 11:3"},"I will give power to my two witnesses, and they will prophesy one thousand and two hundred and sixty days, clothed in\nsackcloth.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 11:4"},"These are the two olive trees and the two lamp stands, standing before the Lord of the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 11:5"},"If anyone desires to harm them, fire proceeds out of their mouth and devours their enemies. If anyone desires to harm\nthem, he must be killed in this way. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 11:6"},"These have the power to shut up the sky, that it may not rain during the days of their prophecy. They have power over the\nwaters, to turn them into blood, and to strike the earth with every plague, as often as they desire.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 11:7"},"When they have finished their testimony, the beast that comes up out of the abyss will make war with them, and overcome\nthem, and kill them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 11:8"},"Their dead bodies will be in the street of the great city, which spiritually is called Sodom and Egypt, where also their\nLord was crucified. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 11:9"},"From amongst the peoples, tribes, languages, and nations, people will look at their dead bodies for three and a half days,\nand will not allow their dead bodies to be laid in a tomb. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 11:10"},"Those who dwell on the earth rejoice over them, and they will be glad. They will give gifts to one another, because these\ntwo prophets tormented those who dwell on the earth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 11:11"},"After the three and a half days, the breath of life from Allah entered into them, and they stood on their feet. Great\nfear fell on those who saw them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 11:12"},"I heard a loud voice from heaven saying to them, “Come up here!” They went up into heaven in the cloud, and their enemies\nsaw them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 11:13"},"In that day there was a great earthquake, and a tenth of the city fell. Seven thousand people were killed in the\nearthquake, and the rest were terrified, and gave glory to Allah of heaven.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 11:14"},"The second woe is past. Behold, the third woe comes quickly.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 11:15"},"The seventh angel sounded, and great voices in heaven followed, saying, “The kingdom of the world has become the Kingdom\nof our Lord, and of his Masih. He will reign forever and ever!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 11:16"},"The twenty-four elders, who sit on their thrones before Allah’s throne, fell on their faces and worshipped Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 11:17"},"saying: “We give you thanks, Lord Allah, the Almighty, the one who is and who\nwas;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “and who is coming”"]}],"caller":"+"}," because you have taken your great power and reigned.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 11:18"},"The nations were angry, and your wrath came, as did the time for the dead to be judged, and to give your bondservants the\nprophets, their reward, as well as to the saints, and those who fear your name, to the small and the great, and to destroy\nthose who destroy the earth.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 11:19"},"Allah’s temple that is in heaven was opened, and the ark of the Lord’s covenant was seen in his temple. Lightnings,\nsounds, thunders, an earthquake, and great hail followed. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"REV 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 12:1"},"A great sign was seen in heaven: a woman clothed with the sun, and the moon under her feet, and on her head a crown of\ntwelve stars. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 12:2"},"She was with child. She cried out in pain, labouring to give birth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 12:3"},"Another sign was seen in heaven. Behold, a great red dragon, having seven heads and ten horns, and on his heads seven\ncrowns. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 12:4"},"His tail drew one third of the stars of the sky, and threw them to the earth. The dragon stood before the woman who was\nabout to give birth, so that when she gave birth he might devour her child.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 12:5"},"She gave birth to a son, a male child, who is to rule all the nations with a rod of iron. Her child was caught up to\nAllah, and to his throne. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 12:6"},"The woman fled into the wilderness, where she has a place prepared by Allah, that there they may nourish her one thousand\nand two hundred and sixty days. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 12:7"},"There was war in the sky. Michael and his angels made war on the dragon. The dragon and his angels made war.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 12:8"},"They didn’t prevail. No place was found for them any more in heaven.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 12:9"},"The great dragon was thrown down, the old serpent, he who is called the Iblis and Shaitan, the deceiver of the whole\nworld. He was thrown down to the earth, and his angels were thrown down with him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 12:10"},"I heard a loud voice in heaven, saying, “Now the salvation, the power, and the Kingdom of our Allah, and the authority of\nhis Masih has come; for the accuser of our brothers has been thrown down, who accuses them before our Allah day and night.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 12:11"},"They overcame him because of the Lamb’s blood, and because of the word of their testimony. They didn’t love their life,\neven to death. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 12:12"},"Therefore rejoice, heavens, and you who dwell in them. Woe to the earth and to the sea, because the Iblis has gone down\nto you, having great wrath, knowing that he has but a short time.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 12:13"},"When the dragon saw that he was thrown down to the earth, he persecuted the woman who gave birth to the male child.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 12:14"},"Two wings of the great eagle were given to the woman, that she might fly into the wilderness to her place, so that she\nmight be nourished for a time, and times, and half a time, from the face of the serpent.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 12:15"},"The serpent spewed water out of his mouth after the woman like a river, that he might cause her to be carried away by the\nstream. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 12:16"},"The earth helped the woman, and the earth opened its mouth and swallowed up the river which the dragon spewed out of his\nmouth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 12:17"},"The dragon grew angry with the woman, and went away to make war with the rest of her\noffspring,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," who keep Allah’s commandments and hold Isa’s testimony.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"REV 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 13:1"},"Then I stood on the sand of the sea. I saw a beast coming up out of the sea, having ten horns and seven heads. On his\nhorns were ten crowns, and on his heads, blasphemous names. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 13:2"},"The beast which I saw was like a leopard, and his feet were like those of a bear, and his mouth like the mouth of a lion.\nThe dragon gave him his power, his throne, and great authority. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 13:3"},"One of his heads looked like it had been wounded fatally. His fatal wound was healed, and the whole earth marvelled at the\nbeast. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 13:4"},"They worshipped the dragon, because he gave his authority to the beast, and they worshipped the beast, saying, “Who is\nlike the beast? Who is able to make war with him?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 13:5"},"A mouth speaking great things and blasphemy was given to him. Authority to make war for forty-two months was given to him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 13:6"},"He opened his mouth for blasphemy against Allah, to blaspheme his name, and his dwelling, those who dwell in heaven.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 13:7"},"It was given to him to make war with the saints, and to overcome them. Authority over every tribe, people, language, and\nnation was given to him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 13:8"},"All who dwell on the earth will worship him, everyone whose name has not been written from the foundation of the world in\nthe book of life of the Lamb who has been killed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 13:9"},"If anyone has an ear, let him hear. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 13:10"},"If anyone is to go into captivity, he will go into captivity. If anyone is to be killed with the sword, he must be\nkilled.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “If anyone leads into captivity, into captivity he goes. If anyone will kill with the\nsword, he must be killed with a sword.” instead of “If anyone is to go into captivity, he will go into captivity. If anyone is\nto be killed with the sword, he must be killed.” "]}],"caller":"+"}," Here is the endurance and the faith of the saints.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 13:11"},"I saw another beast coming up out of the earth. He had two horns like a lamb, and he spoke like a dragon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 13:12"},"He exercises all the authority of the first beast in his presence. He makes the earth and those who dwell in it to\nworship the first beast, whose fatal wound was healed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 13:13"},"He performs great signs, even making fire come down out of the sky to the earth in the sight of people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 13:14"},"He deceives my own",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU omits “my own”"]}],"caller":"+"}," people who dwell on the earth because of the signs he was\ngranted to do in front of the beast, saying to those who dwell on the earth that they should make an image to the beast who had\nthe sword wound and lived. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 13:15"},"It was given to him to give breath to it, to the image of the beast, that the image of the beast should both speak, and\ncause as many as wouldn’t worship the image of the beast to be killed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 13:16"},"He causes all, the small and the great, the rich and the poor, and the free and the slave, to be given marks on their\nright hands, or on their foreheads; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 13:17"},"and that no one would be able to buy or to sell, unless he has that mark, which is the name of the beast or the number of\nhis name. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 13:18"},"Here is wisdom. He who has understanding, let him calculate the number of the beast, for it is the number of a man. His\nnumber is six hundred and sixty-six. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14","sid":"REV 14"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 14:1"},"I saw, and behold, the Lamb standing on Mount Zion, and with him a number, one hundred and forty-four thousand, having his\nname, and the name of his Father, written on their foreheads. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 14:2"},"I heard a sound from heaven, like the sound of many waters, and like the sound of a great thunder. The sound which I heard\nwas like that of harpists playing on their harps. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 14:3"},"They sing a new song before the throne, and before the four living creatures and the elders. No one could learn the song\nexcept the one hundred and forty-four thousand, those who had been redeemed out of the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 14:4"},"These are those who were not defiled with women, for they are virgins. These are those who follow the Lamb wherever he\ngoes. These were redeemed by Isa from amongst men, the first fruits to Allah and to the Lamb.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 14:5"},"In their mouth was found no lie, for they are blameless.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “before the throne of Allah”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 14:6"},"I saw an angel flying in mid heaven, having an eternal Good News to proclaim to those who dwell on the earth, and to every\nnation, tribe, language, and people. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 14:7"},"He said with a loud voice, “Fear the Lord, and give him glory; for the hour of his judgement has come. Worship him who\nmade the heaven, the earth, the sea, and the springs of waters!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 14:8"},"Another, a second angel, followed, saying, “Babylon the great has fallen, which has made all the nations to drink of the\nwine of the wrath of her sexual immorality.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 14:9"},"Another angel, a third, followed them, saying with a great voice, “If anyone worships the beast and his image, and\nreceives a mark on his forehead, or on his hand, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 14:10"},"he also will drink of the wine of the wrath of Allah, which is prepared unmixed in the cup of his anger. He will be\ntormented with fire and sulphur in the presence of the holy angels, and in the presence of the Lamb.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 14:11"},"The smoke of their torment goes up forever and ever. They have no rest day and night, those who worship the beast and his\nimage, and whoever receives the mark of his name. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 14:12"},"Here is the perseverance of the saints, those who keep the commandments of Allah, and the faith of Isa.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 14:13"},"I heard a voice from heaven saying, “Write, ‘Blessed are the dead who die in the Lord from now on.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Yes,” says the Spirit, “that they may rest from their labours; for their works follow with them.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 14:14"},"I looked, and saw a white cloud, and on the cloud one sitting like a son of\nman,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["14:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Daniel 7:13"]}],"caller":"+"}," having on his head a golden crown, and in his hand a sharp sickle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 14:15"},"Another angel came out of the temple, crying with a loud voice to him who sat on the cloud, “Send your sickle, and reap;\nfor the hour to reap has come; for the harvest of the earth is ripe!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 14:16"},"He who sat on the cloud thrust his sickle on the earth, and the earth was reaped.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 14:17"},"Another angel came out of the temple which is in heaven. He also had a sharp sickle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 14:18"},"Another angel came out from the altar, he who has power over fire, and he called with a great voice to him who had the\nsharp sickle, saying, “Send your sharp sickle, and gather the clusters of the vine of the earth, for the earth’s grapes are\nfully ripe!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 14:19"},"The angel thrust his sickle into the earth, and gathered the vintage of the earth, and threw it into the great wine press\nof the wrath of Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 14:20"},"The wine press was trodden outside of the city, and blood came out of the wine press, even to the bridles of the horses,\nas far as one thousand and six hundred stadia.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1600 stadia = 296 kilometres or 184\nmiles"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15","sid":"REV 15"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 15:1"},"I saw another great and marvellous sign in the sky: seven angels having the seven last plagues, for in them Allah’s wrath\nis finished. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 15:2"},"I saw something like a sea of glass mixed with fire, and those who overcame the beast, his\nimage,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “his mark,”"]}],"caller":"+"}," and the number of his name, standing on the sea of glass, having harps of\nAllah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 15:3"},"They sang the song of Musa, the servant of Allah, and the song of the Lamb, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Great and marvellous are your works, Lord Allah, the Almighty!\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Righteous and true are your ways, you King of the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 15:4"},"Who wouldn’t fear you, Lord, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and glorify your name? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For you only are holy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For all the nations will come and worship before you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For your righteous acts have been revealed.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 15:5"},"After these things I looked, and the temple of the tabernacle of the testimony in heaven was opened.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 15:6"},"The seven angels who had the seven plagues came out, clothed with pure, bright linen, and wearing golden sashes around\ntheir breasts. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 15:7"},"One of the four living creatures gave to the seven angels seven golden bowls full of the wrath of Allah, who lives forever\nand ever. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 15:8"},"The temple was filled with smoke from the glory of Allah, and from his power. No one was able to enter into the temple\nuntil the seven plagues of the seven angels would be finished. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16","sid":"REV 16"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 16:1"},"I heard a loud voice out of the temple, saying to the seven angels, “Go and pour out the seven bowls of the wrath of Allah\non the earth!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 16:2"},"The first went, and poured out his bowl into the earth, and it became a harmful and evil sore on the people who had the\nmark of the beast, and who worshipped his image. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 16:3"},"The second angel poured out his bowl into the sea, and it became blood as of a dead man. Every living thing in the sea\ndied. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 16:4"},"The third poured out his bowl into the rivers and springs of water, and they became blood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 16:5"},"I heard the angel of the waters saying, “You are righteous, who are and who were, O Holy One, because you have judged\nthese things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 16:6"},"For they poured out the blood of saints and prophets, and you have given them blood to drink. They deserve this.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 16:7"},"I heard the altar saying, “Yes, Lord Allah, the Almighty, true and righteous are your judgements.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 16:8"},"The fourth poured out his bowl on the sun, and it was given to him to scorch men with fire.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 16:9"},"People were scorched with great heat, and people blasphemed the name of Allah who has the power over these plagues. They\ndidn’t repent and give him glory. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 16:10"},"The fifth poured out his bowl on the throne of the beast, and his kingdom was darkened. They gnawed their tongues because\nof the pain, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 16:11"},"and they blasphemed Allah of heaven because of their pains and their sores. They didn’t repent of their works.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 16:12"},"The sixth poured out his bowl on the great river, the Euphrates. Its water was dried up, that the way might be prepared\nfor the kings that come from the sunrise. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 16:13"},"I saw coming out of the mouth of the dragon, and out of the mouth of the beast, and out of the mouth of the false\nprophet, three unclean spirits, something like frogs; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 16:14"},"for they are spirits of demons, performing signs; which go out to the kings of the whole inhabited earth, to gather them\ntogether for the war of that great day of Allah, the Almighty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 16:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, I come like a thief. Blessed is he who watches, and keeps his clothes, so that he doesn’t walk naked, and\nthey see his shame.” "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 16:16"},"He gathered them together into the place which is called in Hebrew, “Megiddo”.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 16:17"},"The seventh poured out his bowl into the air. A loud voice came out of the temple of heaven, from the throne, saying, “It\nis done!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 16:18"},"There were lightnings, sounds, and thunders; and there was a great earthquake, such as has not happened since there were\nmen on the earth, so great an earthquake, and so mighty. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 16:19"},"The great city was divided into three parts, and the cities of the nations fell. Babylon the great was remembered in the\nsight of Allah, to give to her the cup of the wine of the fierceness of his wrath.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 16:20"},"Every island fled away, and the mountains were not found. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 16:21"},"Great hailstones, about the weight of a talent,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:21\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds."]}],"caller":"+"}," came down out of the sky on people. People blasphemed Allah because of the\nplague of the hail, for this plague is exceedingly severe. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17","sid":"REV 17"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 17:1"},"One of the seven angels who had the seven bowls came and spoke with me, saying, “Come here. I will show you the judgement\nof the great prostitute who sits on many waters, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 17:2"},"with whom the kings of the earth committed sexual immorality. Those who dwell in the earth were made drunken with the wine\nof her sexual immorality.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 17:3"},"He carried me away in the Spirit into a wilderness. I saw a woman sitting on a scarlet-coloured beast, full of blasphemous\nnames, having seven heads and ten horns. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 17:4"},"The woman was dressed in purple and scarlet, and decked with gold and precious stones and pearls, having in her hand a\ngolden cup full of abominations and the impurities of the sexual immorality of the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 17:5"},"And on her forehead a name was written, “MYSTERY, BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF THE PROSTITUTES AND OF THE ABOMINATIONS\nOF THE EARTH.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 17:6"},"I saw the woman drunken with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the martyrs of Isa. When I saw her, I wondered\nwith great amazement. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 17:7"},"The angel said to me, “Why do you wonder? I will tell you the mystery of the woman, and of the beast that carries her,\nwhich has the seven heads and the ten horns. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 17:8"},"The beast that you saw was, and is not; and is about to come up out of the abyss and to go into destruction. Those who\ndwell on the earth and whose names have not been written in the book of life from the foundation of the world will marvel when\nthey see that the beast was, and is not, and shall be present.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “yet is” instead of “shall be present”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 17:9"},"Here is the mind that has wisdom. The seven heads are seven mountains on which the woman sits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 17:10"},"They are seven kings. Five have fallen, the one is, the other has not yet come. When he comes, he must continue a little\nwhile. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 17:11"},"The beast that was, and is not, is himself also an eighth, and is of the seven; and he goes to destruction.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 17:12"},"The ten horns that you saw are ten kings who have received no kingdom as yet, but they receive authority as kings with\nthe beast for one hour. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 17:13"},"These have one mind, and they give their power and authority to the beast.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 17:14"},"These will war against the Lamb, and the Lamb will overcome them, for he is Lord of lords, and King of kings, and those\nwho are with him are called chosen and faithful.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 17:15"},"He said to me, “The waters which you saw, where the prostitute sits, are peoples, multitudes, nations, and languages.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 17:16"},"The ten horns which you saw, and the beast, these will hate the prostitute, will make her desolate, will strip her naked,\nwill eat her flesh, and will burn her utterly with fire. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 17:17"},"For Allah has put in their hearts to do what he has in mind, to be of one mind, and to give their kingdom to the beast,\nuntil the words of Allah should be accomplished. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 17:18"},"The woman whom you saw is the great city, which reigns over the kings of the earth.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18","sid":"REV 18"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 18:1"},"After these things, I saw another angel coming down out of the sky, having great authority. The earth was illuminated with\nhis glory. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 18:2"},"He cried with a mighty voice, saying, “Fallen, fallen is Babylon the great, and she has become a habitation of demons, a\nprison of every unclean spirit, and a prison of every unclean and hateful bird!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 18:3"},"For all the nations have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her sexual immorality, the kings of the earth committed sexual\nimmorality with her, and the merchants of the earth grew rich from the abundance of her luxury.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 18:4"},"I heard another voice from heaven, saying, “Come out of her, my people, that you have no participation in her sins, and\nthat you don’t receive of her plagues, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 18:5"},"for her sins have reached to the sky, and Allah has remembered her iniquities.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 18:6"},"Return to her just as she returned, and repay her double as she did, and according to her works. In the cup which she\nmixed, mix to her double. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 18:7"},"However much she glorified herself, and grew wanton, so much give her of torment and mourning. For she says in her heart,\n‘I sit a queen, and am no widow, and will in no way see mourning.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 18:8"},"Therefore in one day her plagues will come: death, mourning, and famine; and she will be utterly burnt with fire; for the\nLord Allah who has judged her is strong. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 18:9"},"The kings of the earth who committed sexual immorality and lived wantonly with her will weep and wail over her, when they\nlook at the smoke of her burning, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 18:10"},"standing far away for the fear of her torment, saying, ‘Woe, woe, the great city, Babylon, the strong city! For your\njudgement has come in one hour.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 18:11"},"The merchants of the earth weep and mourn over her, for no one buys their merchandise any more:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 18:12"},"merchandise of gold, silver, precious stones, pearls, fine linen, purple, silk, scarlet, all expensive wood, every vessel\nof ivory, every vessel made of most precious wood, and of brass, and iron, and marble;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 18:13"},"and cinnamon, incense, perfume, frankincense, wine, olive oil, fine flour, wheat, sheep, horses, chariots, and people’s\nbodies and souls. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 18:14"},"The fruits which your soul lusted after have been lost to you. All things that were dainty and sumptuous have perished\nfrom you, and you will find them no more at all. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 18:15"},"The merchants of these things, who were made rich by her, will stand far away for the fear of her torment, weeping and\nmourning, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 18:16"},"saying, ‘Woe, woe, the great city, she who was dressed in fine linen, purple, and scarlet, and decked with gold and\nprecious stones and pearls! \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 18:17"},"For in an hour such great riches are made desolate.’ Every ship master, and everyone who sails anywhere, and mariners,\nand as many as gain their living by sea, stood far away, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 18:18"},"and cried out as they looked at the smoke of her burning, saying, ‘What is like the great city?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 18:19"},"They cast dust on their heads, and cried, weeping and mourning, saying, ‘Woe, woe, the great city, in which all who had\ntheir ships in the sea were made rich by reason of her great wealth!’ For she is made desolate in one hour.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 18:20"},"“Rejoice over her, O heaven, you saints, apostles, and prophets; for Allah has judged your judgement on her.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 18:21"},"A mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone and cast it into the sea, saying, “Thus with violence will Babylon,\nthe great city, be thrown down, and will be found no more at all.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"REV 18:22"},"The voice of harpists, minstrels, flute players, and trumpeters will be heard no more at all in you. No craftsman, of\nwhatever craft, will be found any more at all in you. The sound of a mill will be heard no more at all in you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"REV 18:23"},"The light of a lamp will shine no more at all in you. The voice of the bridegroom and of the bride will be heard no more\nat all in you; for your merchants were the princes of the earth; for with your sorcery all the nations were deceived.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"REV 18:24"},"In her was found the blood of prophets and of saints, and of all who have been slain on the earth.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19","sid":"REV 19"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 19:1"},"After these things I heard something like a loud voice of a great multitude in heaven, saying, “Hallelujah! Salvation,\npower, and glory belong to our Allah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 19:2"},"for his judgements are true and righteous. For he has judged the great prostitute, who corrupted the earth with her sexual\nimmorality, and he has avenged the blood of his servants at her hand.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 19:3"},"A second said, “Hallelujah! Her smoke goes up forever and ever.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 19:4"},"The twenty-four elders and the four living creatures fell down and worshipped Allah who sits on the throne, saying, “Amen!\nHallelujah!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 19:5"},"A voice came from the throne, saying, “Give praise to our Allah, all you his servants, you who fear him, the small and the\ngreat!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 19:6"},"I heard something like the voice of a great multitude, and like the voice of many waters, and like the voice of mighty\nthunders, saying, “Hallelujah! For the Lord our Allah, the Almighty, reigns!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 19:7"},"Let’s rejoice and be exceedingly glad, and let’s give the glory to him. For the wedding of the Lamb has come, and his wife\nhas made herself ready.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 19:8"},"It was given to her that she would array herself in bright, pure, fine linen: for the fine linen is the righteous acts of\nthe saints. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 19:9"},"He said to me, “Write, ‘Blessed are those who are invited to the wedding supper of the Lamb.’” He said to me, “These are\ntrue words of Allah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 19:10"},"I fell down before his feet to worship him. He said to me, “Look! Don’t do it! I am a fellow bondservant with you and\nwith your brothers who hold the testimony of Isa. Worship Allah, for the testimony of Isa is the Spirit of Prophecy.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 19:11"},"I saw the heaven opened, and behold, a white horse, and he who sat on it is called Faithful and True. In righteousness he\njudges and makes war. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 19:12"},"His eyes are a flame of fire, and on his head are many crowns. He has names written and a name written which no one knows\nbut he himself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 19:13"},"He is clothed in a garment sprinkled with blood. His name is called “The Word of Allah.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 19:14"},"The armies which are in heaven followed him on white horses, clothed in white, pure, fine linen.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 19:15"},"Out of his mouth proceeds a sharp, double-edged sword, that with it he should strike the nations. He will rule them with\nan iron rod.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["19:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 2:9 "]}],"caller":"+"}," He treads the wine press of the fierceness of the wrath of Allah, the Almighty.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 19:16"},"He has on his garment and on his thigh a name written, “KING OF KINGS, AND LORD OF LORDS.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 19:17"},"I saw an angel standing in the sun. He cried with a loud voice, saying to all the birds that fly in the sky, “Come! Be\ngathered together to the great supper of Allah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “supper of the great Allah” instead of “great\nsupper of Allah”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 19:18"},"that you may eat the flesh of kings, the flesh of captains, the flesh of mighty men, and the flesh of horses and of those\nwho sit on them, and the flesh of all men, both free and slave, small and great.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 19:19"},"I saw the beast, and the kings of the earth, and their armies, gathered together to make war against him who sat on the\nhorse, and against his army. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 19:20"},"The beast was taken, and with him the false prophet who worked the signs in his sight, with which he deceived those who\nhad received the mark of the beast and those who worshipped his image. These two were thrown alive into the lake of fire that\nburns with sulphur. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 19:21"},"The rest were killed with the sword of him who sat on the horse, the sword which came out of his mouth. All the birds\nwere filled with their flesh. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20","sid":"REV 20"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 20:1"},"I saw an angel coming down out of heaven, having the key of the abyss and a great chain in his hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 20:2"},"He seized the dragon, the old serpent, which is the Iblis and Iblis, who deceives the whole inhabited earth, and bound him\nfor a thousand years, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 20:3"},"and cast him into the abyss, and shut it, and sealed it over him, that he should deceive the nations no more, until the\nthousand years were finished. After this, he must be freed for a short time.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 20:4"},"I saw thrones, and they sat on them, and judgement was given to them. I saw the souls of those who had been beheaded for\nthe testimony of Isa, and for the word of Allah, and such as didn’t worship the beast nor his image, and didn’t receive the\nmark on their forehead and on their hand. They lived and reigned with Masih for a thousand years.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 20:5"},"The rest of the dead didn’t live until the thousand years were finished. This is the first resurrection.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 20:6"},"Blessed and holy is he who has part in the first resurrection. Over these, the second death has no power, but they will be\npriests of Allah and of Masih, and will reign with him one thousand years.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 20:7"},"And after the thousand years, Shaitan will be released from his prison,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 20:8"},"and he will come out to deceive the nations which are in the four corners of the earth, Gog and Magog, to gather them\ntogether to the war; the number of whom is as the sand of the sea.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 20:9"},"They went up over the width of the earth, and surrounded the camp of the saints, and the beloved city. Fire came down out\nof heaven from Allah and devoured them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 20:10"},"The Iblis who deceived them was thrown into the lake of fire and sulphur, where the beast and the false prophet are also.\nThey will be tormented day and night forever and ever. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 20:11"},"I saw a great white throne, and him who sat on it, from whose face the earth and the heaven fled away. There was found no\nplace for them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 20:12"},"I saw the dead, the great and the small, standing before the throne, and they opened books. Another book was opened,\nwhich is the book of life. The dead were judged out of the things which were written in the books, according to their works.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 20:13"},"The sea gave up the dead who were in it. Death and Hades",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Hell "]}],"caller":"+"}," gave up the dead who were in them. They were judged, each one according to his works.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 20:14"},"Death and Hades",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Hell"]}],"caller":"+"}," were thrown into the lake of fire. This is the second death, the lake of\nfire. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 20:15"},"If anyone was not found written in the book of life, he was cast into the lake of fire.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21","sid":"REV 21"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 21:1"},"I saw a new heaven and a new earth: for the first heaven and the first earth have passed away, and the sea is no more.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 21:2"},"I saw the holy city, New Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from Allah, prepared like a bride adorned for her husband.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 21:3"},"I heard a loud voice out of heaven saying, “Behold, Allah’s dwelling is with people, and he will dwell with them, and they\nwill be his people, and Allah himself will be with them as their Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 21:4"},"He will wipe away every tear from their eyes. Death will be no more; neither will there be mourning, nor crying, nor pain,\nany more. The first things have passed away.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 21:5"},"He who sits on the throne said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, I am making all things\nnew.”"]}," He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Write, for these words of Allah are faithful and true.”\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 21:6"},"He said to me, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I have become the Alpha and the Omega, the Beginning and the\nEnd."]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR and NU read "]},{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["“It is done! I am the Alpha and the Omega, the Beginning and the\nEnd."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I will give freely to him who is thirsty from the spring of the water of life.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 21:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who overcomes, I will give him these things. I will be his Allah, and he will be my son.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 21:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But for the cowardly, unbelieving, sinners, abominable, murderers, sexually immoral,\nsorcerers,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “sorcerers” here also includes users of potions and\ndrugs."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["idolaters, and all liars, their part is in the lake that burns with fire and sulphur, which is the second\ndeath.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 21:9"},"One of the seven angels who had the seven bowls, who were loaded with the seven last plagues came, and he spoke with me,\nsaying, “Come here. I will show you the wife, the Lamb’s bride.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 21:10"},"He carried me away in the Spirit to a great and high mountain, and showed me the holy city, Jerusalem, coming down out of\nheaven from Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 21:11"},"having the glory of Allah. Her light was like a most precious stone, as if it were a jasper stone, clear as crystal;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 21:12"},"having a great and high wall; having twelve gates, and at the gates twelve angels; and names written on them, which are\nthe names of the twelve tribes of the children of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 21:13"},"On the east were three gates; and on the north three gates; and on the south three gates; and on the west three gates.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 21:14"},"The wall of the city had twelve foundations, and on them twelve names of the twelve Apostles of the Lamb.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 21:15"},"He who spoke with me had for a measure a golden reed to measure the city, its gates, and its walls.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 21:16"},"The city is square, and its length is as great as its width. He measured the city with the reed, twelve thousand and\ntwelve stadia.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["12,012 stadia = or 2,221 kilometres or 1,380 miles. TR reads 12,000 stadia instead of 12,012\nstadia."]}],"caller":"+"}," Its length, width, and height are equal. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 21:17"},"Its wall is one hundred and forty-four cubits,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:17\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["144 cubits is about 65.8 metres or 216 feet"]}],"caller":"+"}," by the measure of a man, that is, of an angel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 21:18"},"The construction of its wall was jasper. The city was pure gold, like pure glass.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 21:19"},"The foundations of the city’s wall were adorned with all kinds of precious stones. The first foundation was jasper; the\nsecond, sapphire;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, lapis lazuli"]}],"caller":"+"}," the third, chalcedony; the fourth, emerald;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 21:20"},"the fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, sardius; the seventh, chrysolite; the eighth, beryl; the ninth, topaz; the tenth,\nchrysoprase; the eleventh, jacinth; and the twelfth, amethyst. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 21:21"},"The twelve gates were twelve pearls. Each one of the gates was made of one pearl. The street of the city was pure gold,\nlike transparent glass. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"REV 21:22"},"I saw no temple in it, for the Lord Allah, the Almighty, and the Lamb, are its temple.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"REV 21:23"},"The city has no need for the sun or moon to shine, for the very glory of Allah illuminated it, and its lamp is the Lamb.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"REV 21:24"},"The nations will walk in its light. The kings of the earth bring the glory and honour of the nations into it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"REV 21:25"},"Its gates will in no way be shut by day (for there will be no night there),\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"REV 21:26"},"and they shall bring the glory and the honour of the nations into it so that they may enter.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"REV 21:27"},"There will in no way enter into it anything profane, or one who causes an abomination or a lie, but only those who are\nwritten in the Lamb’s book of life. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22","sid":"REV 22"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"REV 22:1"},"He showed me a",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “pure”"]}],"caller":"+"}," river of water of life, clear as crystal, proceeding out of the throne\nof Allah and of the Lamb, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"REV 22:2"},"in the middle of its street. On this side of the river and on that was the tree of life, bearing twelve kinds of fruits,\nyielding its fruit every month. The leaves of the tree were for the healing of the nations.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"REV 22:3"},"There will be no curse any more. The throne of Allah and of the Lamb will be in it, and his servants will serve him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"REV 22:4"},"They will see his face, and his name will be on their foreheads.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"REV 22:5"},"There will be no night, and they need no lamp light or sun light; for the Lord Allah will illuminate them. They will reign\nforever and ever. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"REV 22:6"},"He said to me, “These words are faithful and true. The Lord Allah of the spirits of the prophets sent his angel to show to\nhis bondservants the things which must happen soon.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"REV 22:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, I come quickly. Blessed is he who keeps the words of the prophecy of this\nbook.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"REV 22:8"},"Now I, Yuhanna, am the one who heard and saw these things. When I heard and saw, I fell down to worship before the feet of\nthe angel who had shown me these things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"REV 22:9"},"He said to me, “See you don’t do it! I am a fellow bondservant with you and with your brothers, the prophets, and with\nthose who keep the words of this book. Worship Allah.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"REV 22:10"},"He said to me, “Don’t seal up the words of the prophecy of this book, for the time is at hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"REV 22:11"},"He who acts unjustly, let him act unjustly still. He who is filthy, let him be filthy still. He who is righteous, let him\ndo righteousness still. He who is holy, let him be holy still.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"REV 22:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, I come quickly. My reward is with me, to repay to each man according to his work.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"REV 22:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"REV 22:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Blessed are those who do his commandments,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:14\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU reads “wash their robes” instead of “do his commandments”."]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that they may have the right to the tree of life, and may enter in by the gates into the city.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"REV 22:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Outside are the dogs, the sorcerers, the sexually immoral, the murderers, the idolaters, and everyone who loves and\npractices falsehood. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"REV 22:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I, Isa, have sent my angel to testify these things to you for the assemblies. I am the root and the offspring of\nDawood, the Bright and Morning Star.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"REV 22:17"},"The Spirit and the bride say, “Come!” He who hears, let him say, “Come!” He who is thirsty, let him come. He who desires,\nlet him take the water of life freely. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"REV 22:18"},"I testify to everyone who hears the words of the prophecy of this book, if anyone adds to them, may Allah add to him the\nplagues which are written in this book. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"REV 22:19"},"If anyone takes away from the words of the book of this prophecy, may Allah take away his part from the\ntree",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “Book” instead of “tree”"]}],"caller":"+"}," of life, and out of the holy city, which are written in this book.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"REV 22:20"},"He who testifies these things says, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Yes, I come quickly.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Amen! Yes, come, Lord Isa. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"REV 22:21"},"The grace of the Lord Al Masih Isa be with all the saints. Amen.\n"]}]}